Package: ScikitNB
Type: Package
Title: A R package of Naive Bayesian Classifiers models inspired from Scikit-Learn
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Bourhani Dounya [Master 2 SISE - Lyon 2], Steiner Fiona [Master 2 SISE - Lyon 2] & Varangot-Reille Clovis [Master 2 SISE - Lyon 2]
Maintainer: The package maintainer are Bourhani Dounya <dounya.bourhani@univ-lyon2.fr>, 
				       Steiner Fiona <fiona.steiner@univ-lyon2.fr> 
				       and Varangot-Reille Clovis <c.varangot@univ-lyon2.fr>
Description: Implements Gaussian Naive Bayes Classifier, Bernoulli Naive Bayes Classifier, and Categorical Naive Bayes Classifier in R, 
    providing a comprehensive solution for classification problems. This package 
    is capable of handling numerical, categorical, mixed (numerical and categorical), and text data types, 
    making it versatile for a wide range of applications. The implementation 
    utilizes the R6 class system.
Imports:
    caret,
    corrplot,
    discretization,
    FactoMineR,
    Matrix,
    parallel,
    R6,
    tidyverse,
    tm,
    wordcloud
